theorem Topology.subset_closure_interior_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (interior A))) := by
  intro x hxA
  -- `x` lies in `closure (interior A)` since every set is contained in the closure of its interior.
  have hx_cl : x ∈ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := subset_closure hxA
  -- Enlarge the target set using the monotonicity lemma with `A := interior A`.
  have h_incl :
      closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆
        closure (interior (closure (interior A))) := by
    simpa [interior_interior] using
      (Topology.closure_interior_subset_closure_interior_closure
        (X := X) (A := interior A))
  -- Conclude the desired membership.
  exact h_incl hx_cl
